The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 City meet live on TV

Bangalore: Mahesh Bhupathis Globosport on Tuesday announced its partnership with leading sports channel TEN Sports, giving it the exclusive broadcasting rights for the Sunfeast Open 2005 WTA Tour event in Calcutta from September 19 to 25. 

The tie-up was announced by Bhupathi and Peter Hutton, vice-president, programming, TEN Sports, at a news conference where the Sunfeast Open Logo for the $170,000 event was also unveiled. 

TEN Sports will telecast the tournament live for seven days, Bhupathi, whose Globosport is the tournament promoters, said. 

Terming the broadcasting rights for TEN Sports as the Highlight of the Year after its signing of contracts for the French Open and US Open, Hutton said: We want to promote this event as the top international event like French Open and US Open. 

The logo captures the essence of the brand Sunfeast against the historic landmark of Calcutta ? Howrah Bridge, which forms the backdrop of the design. 

 (PTI) 




